Pakistani food in a pizza place setting.  Food pretty delicious, as authentic as it gets.  Fast and cheap. We loved the butter chicken. But atmosphere is a true zero, with the cheapest possible construction materials used for floor, walls and ceiling, the bare minimum of decor ( framed mosques and prayers). Paper plates and forks. Workers/ owner are nice and friendly. Clientele mostly speaking and looking Pakistani. Huge selection of desserts that appear mostly to be made of sugar, milk and coconut. All in all, a nice experience, that makes you feel like you've gone to another country for lunch.

I love this place for a few reasons.  You can see all the food in front of you and choose based on what you see. 4 people can eat a ton of food here for less than $20. The roti and naan are baked for you when you order them.  7 minutes later you'll get fresh hot bread. Call 15 min. ahead and get lamb or chicken cooked fresh for you.  A whole chicken is something like $10. As with most of the restaurants in little Pakistan the food is a bit too oily for my taste, so I choose dishes based on the amount of oil. Samosas are 50 cents.  Yup 50 cents.  They are best around 11 am when they come out of the fryer, and a few other points during the day. I stay away from most of the sweets, but the rice pudding and mango pudding are solid. Good chai. Friendly service!
